cs.NE, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper involves decoding EEG signals to control a machine learning model and a biomechanical model.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper deals with controlling the fundamental frequency of a vocal sound synthesizer.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the paper involves the interaction between human kinematics and machine learning/biomechanical models.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper involves a biomechanical arm prototype.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper involves a closed loop neuro-biomechanical control scheme.
